race.comment: GREENIDGE (9) was a south east winner fresh then finished a fading last in town. This is a much easier and off a decent draw will take catching. JILLADORA (5) was midfield last time in town at the last two. Probably going better than it looks and despite a wide draw can give a sight. FALAISE (12) had almost a year off before returning over 1200m in town and wasn't disgraced. Much better for it and has placed 2/3 second-up. Extra trip is a huge plus. DOTHRAKI (11)  has been racing in richer company and has started big odds the last two, jumping from very wide draws at each. Much better suited here, down in weight and finally draws a gate. Can improve sharply.
